&lt;div class="mb-4"&gt;
 &lt;h1 class="text-center mb-1"&gt;Personalpronomen&lt;/h1&gt;
 &lt;h4 class="text-center text-muted"&gt;German Personal Pronouns&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="table-responsive mb-4"&gt;
 &lt;table class="table table-bordered"&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th class="case-header-nom text-center p-3"&gt;NOMINATIV&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th class="case-header-akk text-center p-3"&gt;AKKUSATIV&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th class="case-header-dat text-center p-3"&gt;DATIV&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td class="p-3"&gt;
 &lt;div class="rule-text"&gt;Used when the pronoun is the &lt;strong&gt;subject&lt;/strong&gt; (doing the action).&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="example-text"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Du&lt;/span&gt; lernst Deutsch.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="example-text"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sie&lt;/span&gt; liest ein Buch.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td class="p-3"&gt;
 &lt;div class="rule-text"&gt;Used when the pronoun is the &lt;strong&gt;direct object&lt;/strong&gt; (receiving the action).&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="example-text"&gt;Er sieht &lt;span&gt;dich&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="example-text"&gt;Sie ruft &lt;span&gt;mich&lt;/span&gt; an.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td class="p-3"&gt;
 &lt;div class="rule-text"&gt;Used when the pronoun is the &lt;strong&gt;indirect object&lt;/strong&gt; (to/for whom).&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="example-text"&gt;Ich helfe &lt;span&gt;dir&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="example-text"&gt;Wir danken &lt;span&gt;euch&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
 &lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
